LUKSbox build-time placeholder. The real LICENSE-WINFSP.txt is fetched
verbatim from the WinFsp upstream repository at release-build time and
written next to LUKSbox.msi + LUKSboxSetup.exe. See the
"Fetch upstream WinFsp license text" step in .github/workflows/release.yml.

Why fetched-not-committed:
  - WinFsp is GPLv3 with a non-GPL-app linking exception. The full
    license text is owned by upstream and any divergence in this repo
    (typos, formatting drift) would be a misrepresentation of their
    terms. Fetching at build time guarantees byte-identical text from
    the WinFsp tag we are bundling (currently v2.0).
  - Source URL (pinned to the same tag the bundled MSI comes from):
        https://raw.githubusercontent.com/winfsp/winfsp/v2.0/License.txt

If you are reading this template in a built artifact, something went
wrong with the release pipeline. The .exe / .zip would not normally
ship this file; only the upstream-verbatim LICENSE-WINFSP.txt.
